---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Safety & COR Certification | Alpine Drywall (Calgary) Ltd." description="COR certified since 2001, NCSO on staff, daily field level hazard assessments and toolbox talks. A site that runs safe runs fast." active="safety" canonical="https://alpinedrywallcalgary.com/safety.html">
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="eyebrow">Safety</span>
        <h1>A site that runs safe runs fast.</h1>
        <p class="lead">Forty years on commercial projects, and the safety culture that comes with them.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 0;">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="cor-block">
          <div class="cor-logo"><img src="/assets/images/cor.png" alt="COR Certificate of Recognition" width="160" height="160" loading="lazy" /></div>
          <div>
            <span class="eyebrow">COR Certified</span>
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Certificate of Recognition since 2001.</h2>
            <p>The Certificate of Recognition is the construction industry's benchmark for a working health and safety management system. The COR program launched in 1992. Alpine has held the certification continuously since 2001.</p>
            <p>That isn't a binder on a shelf. It's an annual external audit, ongoing training records, and a documented field program that has held up across hundreds of commercial jobs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">On every site</span>
          <h2>Three things we do daily, no exceptions.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="protocol-grid">
          <article class="protocol">
            <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"/></svg></div>
            <h3>Field level hazard assessment</h3>
            <p>Before tools are lifted, the crew walks the area, identifies the hazards specific to that day's work, and documents the controls. Written every shift, signed off by the foreman.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="protocol">
            <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg></div>
            <h3>Toolbox talks</h3>
            <p>Short, focused, daily safety briefings. The whole crew is aligned on what's happening that day, what's running near them, and what to watch for in their area.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="protocol">
            <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M19.4 15a1.65 1.65 0 0 0 .33 1.82l.06.06a2 2 0 1 1-2.83 2.83l-.06-.06a1.65 1.65 0 0 0-1.82-.33 1.65 1.65 0 0 0-1 1.51V21a2 2 0 0 1-4 0v-.09A1.65 1.65 0 0 0 9 19.4a1.65 1.65 0 0 0-1.82.33l-.06.06a2 2 0 1 1-2.83-2.83l.06-.06a1.65 1.65 0 0 0 .33-1.82 1.65 1.65 0 0 0-1.51-1H3a2 2 0 0 1 0-4h.09A1.65 1.65 0 0 0 4.6 9a1.65 1.65 0 0 0-.33-1.82l-.06-.06a2 2 0 1 1 2.83-2.83l.06.06a1.65 1.65 0 0 0 1.82.33H9a1.65 1.65 0 0 0 1-1.51V3a2 2 0 0 1 4 0v.09a1.65 1.65 0 0 0 1 1.51 1.65 1.65 0 0 0 1.82-.33l.06-.06a2 2 0 1 1 2.83 2.83l-.06.06a1.65 1.65 0 0 0-.33 1.82V9c.36.16.66.43.86.78"/></svg></div>
            <h3>Owned, inspected equipment</h3>
            <p>Because we own the fleet, we control the maintenance schedule. Lifts, scaffolding, and finishing equipment come to your site inspected and certified, not rented and unknown.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-dark">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">Certifications &amp; programs</span>
          <h2>What's on the wall, and why it matters to you.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pillars">
          <article class="pillar" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
            <h3>COR Certified, audited annually</h3>
            <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">Independent external audits keep the safety program honest. The program is run, not displayed.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="pillar" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
            <h3>NCSO on staff</h3>
            <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">A National Construction Safety Officer is part of the team, not a contractor we call when there's an incident.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="pillar" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
            <h3>Ongoing crew training</h3>
            <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">Fall protection, aerial work platform, WHMIS, first aid: tracked, renewed, and current for every active crew member.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
